This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category as it focuses on enabling a robot to learn object manipulation by imitation. It also involves Reinforcement Learning (RL), which is a common technique used in robotics. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as segmentation and policy learning, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

Additionally, the paper involves computer vision techniques as it relies on external observations of demonstrations, which could fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. 

Finally, the paper involves system engineering as it aims to develop a system that can effectively learn and execute object manipulation tasks, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
